webpackJsonp([0xa0e366c5301b],{388:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:"<h3>👋 everyone,</h3>\n<h1>Donating with TinyMerch</h1>\n<p>When we were building TinyMerch, our goal was to make selling physical products\non your website as quick and easy as possible. We wanted the barrier to entry to\nbe nonexistent, anyone with a site could sell merch directly to visitors.</p>\n<p>For many people, this creates a revenue stream that requires no effort on their\npart to maintain or operate. That's an incredibly exciting statement to make,\nand not many companies get to use a statement like that in their marketing. But\nthere was one piece of advice we received early on that seemed so perfect we\ncouldn't help but try and implement it. That feedback was to add an option to\ndonate profits to charity!</p>\n<p>This advice felt like a no-brainer. It allows people to quickly set up a\nfundraiser and start raising money, not just for themselves, but as a way of\nhelping others.</p>\n<p>So to start, we're offering the option to donate profits to ricebowls. An\namazing non-profit based in our own beautiful Greenville, SC. Ricebowls works to\nprovide food to orphanges around the world.</p>\n<p>We're actively working to add more charities to this list all the time! If\nthere's a charity you'd like to see on this list,\n<a href=\"mailto:team@tinymerch.com\">let us know</a>, and we'll do our best to continue and\nexpand our options.</p>\n<p>Interested in getting these updates in your inbox?\n(<a href=\"https://www.producthunt.com/upcoming/tiny-merch\">Sign Up for Our Newsletter</a>)</p>\n<p>✌️ Best, The TinyMerch Team</p>",frontmatter:{date:"November 29, 2017",path:"/blog/donations",title:"Giving Back Made Simplier"}}},pathContext:{prev:{html:'<h3>👋 everyone,</h3>\n<h1>Meet TinyMerch, our 2017 PH Hackathon Submission.</h1>\n<p>Selling physical products comes with a full set of headaches: printing,\ninventory, overhead, maintenance, returns, shipping 🚚, and it usually means\nrebuilding your site or sending customers to another platform. Simply put, it’s\na big commitment.</p>\n<p>TinyMerch solves this. You don’t have to change your website. You never pay a\nsubscription fee. You don’t handle inventory or shipping. We process orders, get\nthe products printed on-demand, ship them to customers, and send you the profits\n💸.</p>\n<p>For artists 👨‍🎨, bands 🎸, or small businesses 🏪, selling merch shouldn’t be a\nfull-time job, and TinyMerch is designed to make the process as fast and easy as\npossible. You can be up and running, selling t-shirts directly on your website\nin 5 minutes.</p>\n<p><strong>image</strong></p>\n<p>With TinyMerch you choose a product, upload a custom design, set the price, and\nit’s instantly available for purchase in your custom store. Paste a small embed\nscript onto your website, and customers can purchase the products you just\ndesigned.</p>\n<p>TinyMerch is perfect for limited runs, promotions, or to simply add a store to\nyour website for the holidays 🎄. There’s no inventory, no monthly fee, no\nhassle or worry about staying on top of orders and fulfillment. We take care of\nall of this for you!</p>\n<p><strong>TinyMerch provides a worry-free way to start selling custom merch.</strong></p>\n<h3>So How Does TinyMerch Work?</h3>\n<p>TinyMerch is a simple ecommerce platform that integrates with on-demand printing\nand fulfillment services. Users create an account, add products, and get a\ncustom embed code to add to their sites. We use Stripe Connect to make it easy\nfor users to get paid securely when customers buy the products they make.</p>\n<p>Current ecommerce platforms are built for larger companies. We created TinyMerch\nfor the little guys: content creators, artists, bands, and small businesses.\nYou’re who we made TinyMerch for! <strong>You’re who we made TinyMerch for!</strong></p>\n<h3>See a Demo Store:</h3>\n<p>If you want to see a store in action you can checkout the Demo Store on\n<a href="https://tinymerch.com/demo">tinymerch.com</a></p>\n<h3>See a Demo Store:</h3>\n<p>Already convinced this is for you? You can\n<a href="https://my.tinymerch.com">Get Started Now!</a> and have a store on your site\nselling 💯 original content in a matter of minutes!</p>\n<p>Interested in getting these updates in your inbox?\n(<a href="https://www.producthunt.com/upcoming/tiny-merch">Sign Up for Our Newsletter</a>)</p>\n<p>✌️ Best, The TinyMerch Team</p>',id:"/Users/aeryk/Sites/Nicer/TinyMerch/tinymerch/website/src/pages/11-30-2017-upcoming-03/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",frontmatter:{date:"2017-11-30",path:"/blog/ph-hackathon",tags:["fourth"],title:"2017 PH Hackathon",postTitle:"Hello Again",postGreeting:"👋 everyone,",postPreview:"Selling physical products comes with a full set of headaches: printing, inventory, overhead, maintenance, returns, shipping 🚚, and it usually means rebuilding your site or sending customers to another platform. Simply put, it’s a big commitment. . ."}},next:{html:'<h3>👋 everyone,</h3>\n<h1>Hello Again</h1>\n<p>Just a quick update on progress here at TinyMerch. We’ve been hard at work this past week building out a lot of the nitty-gritty innards that\'ll make TinyMerch function. Stuff like setting up Firebase functions, generating print files, connecting with APIs, etc, etc. 😴</p>\n<p>Anyways, on to a couple of the more exciting aspects of TinyMerch. We\'ll be spinning up a TinyMerch Blog (Launching next week!) where we’ll be regularly posting updates, along with helpful tips on setting up your store. We’ve also been working on rounding out our Product Catalog for the Hackathon Launch. We’re currently looking to launch with shirts, prints, and digital files. But what are some things you’d like to see? Let us know in the survey below!</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/product-94eaf0d06c1efcdb1218dbd785570885-8189c.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 63.315217391304344%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Product Example"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/product-94eaf0d06c1efcdb1218dbd785570885-fb8a0.png"\n        srcset="/static/product-94eaf0d06c1efcdb1218dbd785570885-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/product-94eaf0d06c1efcdb1218dbd785570885-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/product-94eaf0d06c1efcdb1218dbd785570885-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/product-94eaf0d06c1efcdb1218dbd785570885-8189c.png 736w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Another exciting announcement we’d like to share is that TinyMerch will allow sellers to donate their proceeds to charity! With the holidays coming up and many people in need around the world, we created a simple and easy outlet to allow content creators and businesses to donate to select charities with the click of a button. As we finish setting this up, we\'d love to hear from you all about which charities you\'d wish to see available for donations.</p>\n<p>(And for the less benevolent amongst you. . .The answer is yes, our accountant has said this would most likely be deductible.)</p>\n<h3>Feedback Survey:</h3>\n<p><a href="https://goo.gl/forms/t8K8xDOgWTOry5Ew1">https://goo.gl/forms/t8K8xDOgWTOry5Ew1</a></p>\n<p>Interested in getting these updates in your inbox?\n(<a href="https://www.producthunt.com/upcoming/tiny-merch">Sign Up for Our Newsletter</a>)</p>\n<p>✌️ Best,\nThe Tiny Team</p>',id:"/Users/aeryk/Sites/Nicer/TinyMerch/tinymerch/website/src/pages/11-17-2017-upcoming-02/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",frontmatter:{date:"2017-11-17",path:"/blog/upcoming-02",tags:["second"],title:"Tiny Update #02",postTitle:"Hello Again",postGreeting:"👋 everyone,",postPreview:"Just a quick update on progress here at TinyMerch. We’ve been hard at work this past week building out a lot of the nitty-gritty innards that’ll make TinyMerch function. Stuff like setting up Firebase functions, generating print files, connecting with APIs. . ."}}}}}});
